tip.text: Tasty African meals, ~€15 per dish. A terrace outside
A zucchini eggplant soup with goat cheese & chickpeas:
A cozy cafe, vegetarian meals and healthy desserts. The carrot cake has a very plain taste, not sweet.
Tasty these days for lunch: shrimps salade & sausages with potato-carrots purée
Desserts buffet is my weakness! 😅 cakes, puddings, pancakes, ice-creams, chocolate fondue
The Lebanese croque is tasty and big. A difference from the regular croque - it's in a kind of a whole-grain pita bread. ~€11
A vegetarian lasagna has a strong taste, you really don't notice the absence of meat (replaced with a quorn)
A very nice resto, spacious, stylish. Their speciality is a Belgian dish "Stoverij" in a beer sauce, but with the chicken meat instead of a pork.
A wonderful domain to walk, have a picnic. On a sunny spring day it's also crazily crowded - people come like crazy with their baskets and thermoses 🌮🍏☕️ 😄
The cakes are a lot better here than at Julie's house. They cost ~ €6 though.
Trendy interior 👍
Tasty less traditional pizza, with unusual combinations, like salmon with beats, or chicken with fennel. Around €15 each
Not bad. Linguine with shrimps:
There's a nice cafe in this library, but not so cheap - €5,5 for a piece of cake
Cozy resto, good service. Around €18 for a meal. You won't regret the curry-rice (more spicy and sweet creamy taste), or this shrimp-rice (for a saltier taste) :
Good breakfast, many variations. Cozy atmosphere
There's only pasta here (no pizza). But it's a good quality. We took pasta within shrimps and pasta with meatballs. Both were tasty prepared.
Latte macchiato is tasty and large
Very good soup+bread (grilled and tasting with some spices) for lunch!
Francisco Goya's paintings are here now. Together with some Iranian artist who worked in a similar style. Come have a look

venue.name: Museum of Fine Arts (MSK) (Museum voor Schone Kunsten (MSK))

tip.text: There's a new sculpture of a sleeping baby with a dog. Under a cobblestone cover 😊
A bowl of tasty soup-purée with bread is €4,8. Long queues between 12 and 2 pm
The coffee and the cakes are very good here. But the service is terrible: it's sooo slow. There's only one waitress that had to be reminded 3 times that my coffee has to be deca. And one lazy barista
Good quality & more expensive products.
Special spring bouquets 🌱
A view from the roof top
In 1920's they used to show movies on this "curtain". How sweet is that 👵🏼👴🏻
There's a number of large & gorgeous concert halls inside! All in art-nouveau style
Pastas here are from €17,5 to ~ €20. I've tried the wide one with lots of tuna and a garlic-veggie sauce: it's delicious and a portion is large. 🍝
A cozy resto in the centre of Kortrijk, huge portions, really tasty well prepared meals. This large thin crispy pizza with really lots of tuna was ~ €12
You can have a mini guided tour here (from 9 persons), with 3 bier tasting
The warm dish which is payed appart from the buffet option:  salmon in pastry dough with baked potato (~€16)
The warm dish which is payed appart from the buffet option: chicken with bacon and potato crockets (~€16)
The brasserie of the museum is very decent: here's the hunmmus sandwiches and the quiche-pie with Brussels sprouts. ~€10 each.

venue.name: S.M.A.K. | Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst

tip.text: Quite nice, trendy coffee bar. Nothing mind-blowing, just a good coffee and a few desserts
This is the "Teppanyaki" option: you choose a fresh fish/seafood and a cook fries it in front of you. You can have pieces of scallops, shrimps, frog legs, sole fish 🍤🐢🐠
There's a fresh wok option here: you take fresh seafood/fish, veggies and noodles and a cook woks it for you with a sauce of your choice 👍
A spacious family resto with a huge dinner buffet of Thai cuisine (and also French fries, croquets and salads)
The variety of food is quite good. And it's not just cold sandwiches 👍
A very nice spacious lounge zone with modern interior and meals-buffet
The waiters serve the food really quick, thanks 🏅. On a photo - vegetarian spinach ball with mashed potato, ~€13
A trendy place to have a lunch for ~ €13 (still water and an apple included). The concept is simple - a "ball" of your choice (a côtelette) with a side dish of your choice (purée or a salad)
The "coffee cake" is delicious with a lot of Philadelphia cheese. The portion of an apple pie is Huge! Around ₴70 each
The camomile-mint-passion fruit tea was delicious.
The eggplant rolls are one delicious appetizer 😍
Мидии с овощами в соусе карри. Неплохо, но довольно остро. Mussels with veggies in curry sauce. It wasn't bad but watch out - quite spicy.
Yammi, I want it all. I loved the "coffee cake" - worth a try if you enjoy the chocolate taste with a few dough
I come to this place every time as to my fav Klondike of desserts. Even in Belgium you'd never find that huge choice of good quality desserts in one place
⛵️ Choose the right details to build your boat and see if it sinks or not
There are simple theme games and tasks here: for example: smell the boxes and guess what good that is (smth that was widely exported from Madeira in 16th cent.).
A history of Madeira in an interactive and game manner
The lobster&speck risotto was not bad, but seriously, there were 5 gr of lobster in total. The orange zest instead was too dominating - a risotto isn't supposed to taste like the orange juice, heh?
This is a "vegetarian pizza". The waiter didn't inform about it's shape. Sorry - i want my pizza in a shape of a pizza! The taste was also poor - the supposed pesto sauce was hardly there.
The pastry here isn't perfect (well nowhere in Madeira is), but the almond-chocolate cookies are worth a try
People advise here the "Palmiers cake" - it's more a breakfast thing rather than a dessert. Imagine a sandwich of a puff dough with Nutella in between. And it's huge indeed, take it for two 👭
I don't find this a super quality bakery. Rather an average. But the stuff is friendly of course
Chicken stuffed with lobster was good, with a tasty sauce. Potatoes&veggies on a side
Nice restaurant with a live music from 7pm. Very social funny waiters. The main dish ~ €12-17
The lobby:
A view from the room with a sea-view (you have to pay additionally for it)
A pool-view
It's a nice clean hotel with clean spacious rooms and extended breakfast-buffet. It's a good value for money, I don't see why it's got so few points on Foursquare. It's been recently renovated.
Mackerel fillet is fried and served in a vinegar sauce with the corn porridge
Good food ,a wide choice of "fish of the day". They often serve it with a corn porridge (a bit like Italian polenta) - cooked (white cubes) or fried (yellow cubes). Fried one's got more taste
A deer with mushrooms, baked appel and mashed potato:
A bit more chique type of brasserie - in an old style building with high ceilings and large chandelier. The serving is at a higher level, too. Warm main dishes: €21..- €30
I'm not a fan of Chinese cuisine, apart from their bami-goreng and mi-goreng. And they are great here! Big portions, tasty cooked noodles with lots of meat or shrimps 🍜  ~ €15/portion
Enjoy some waffles or mussels (or both) at the coast! 👏
Amazing hospital! I haven't seen more modern and beautiful state hospitals than this.
Good pizza, with a possibility to order a "mini" one (with a salad on side), and a "half-half" one: 2 pizzas in one, if you can't choose. A bit slow service
Tasty not expensive Indian food. We liked the meal with eggplants (aubergine), and chicken korma
Plat du jour was super tasty: a quality of a restaurant meal with a fountain of tastes for 9,5€ 👍
Nice cafe, tasty meals, big portions of salads and a tasty cake "3 chocolates". Not pricey
A yellow curry rice with chicken - more sweet, and fried rice with chicken - more salty. Both are well prepared.
Love their desserts.
Very tasty salads - prepared (~13€) or self-chosen (~14€). Big portions
I love to have a weekend breakfast here. Cozy terrace by the river and this Egg Benedict 👌
It's a very atmospheric place, for a meal or coffee in the old centre of Ghent
Chocomilk with croissants - a nice Sunday breakfast. Not obligatory to do a laundry :)
Tasty desserts but very slooow service.
The cakes in its local cafe aren't really good. You better stick to coffee 😉
Tasty meals and desserts. On a pic: lemon cake and browny
A new cake "choko-roll" (or smth like that) is unbelievable. For chocolate connaisseurs! Three milks tasty too, as usual
Here is the vegetarian wok, plus a plate of rice with a few veggies on a side
Greek Moussaka - reminds a lasagna, with potato layer instead of pasta. With minced meat and veggies

venue.name: S.M.A.K. | Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst

tip.text: A very nice apartment, cozy and beautiful interior. The bedroom is a bit too small but the mattress is good. Central location but it's still quite because it overlooks the inner yard
Tasty omelette and crispy fresh croissants for breakfast. Affordable prices. The service is a bit too slow, especially in the weekend morning
Gorgeous train station
It's a paradise park where you can also observe animals, fish, replies, birds
I liked the "advokaat" it's homemade and thick
I enjoyed the shrimps with steamed veggies and rice - super flavour, not too spicy and many big shrimps 👍🍤
The chicken yellow curry was delicious and not too spicy 👌
I accidentally took "Emmy's favorite" but didn't regret - it's very tasty fluffy and crispy
The goat cheese salad with chickpeas is a recent and very delicious. The goat cheese is warm and not too strong
A veal steak served with veggies and fries = 30€
Cozy place, good food
You can get amazing retro-style soft toys here. Quite expensive because it's a good quality handmade
Beautiful bouquets, stylish interior objects, friendly ladies
We could smell the tasty breakfast in the room, when we woke up. Downstairs super fresh croissants, freshly squeezed oranges juice and other things were waiting for us.
I think it's the best B&B of the coast. It's clean and super cozy - as if you came to visit your mom. A home-baked apple pie for you at any time. Tasty breakfast
We walked along the coast, from De Haan to the next town ~ about 6km. There had a coffe, and came back by tram. It's a nice place! 🌊 💙
The rooms interior is a modern classic. There are certain small defects in the room which a 5* isn't allowed to have, but in general it's super clean and cozy.
The interior of the hotel is I classic and cozy, the sofas are soft as a pile of snow, - very pleasant place to stay
Some details in the room are confusing if it's really 5*, but I don't find it critical. The rest is amazing - very clean bathroom, bed linen, super varied tasty breakfast.
The pool is very nice here - located on the 8th floor, it's large (with the swimming lines) and nicely illuminated at night.

tip.text: The yoga class and the gym are here on the upper floor, with such an amazing view. In case I don't like Kuala Lumpur - I have smth to occupy myself with!
This is a LE-Wait-For-it-GENDARY hotel. Huge (116 sq.m) modern clean flat. Kitchen. Washing machine. Cleaning every day. Various breakfast. Many activities: gym, billiards, pool, sauna and Jacuzzi
One of that Asian restaurants where the cockroaches and rats are running around but the food is tasty 😐
The BBQ plate - was a tasty set of chicken and lamb. Together with the eggplants and steamed rice. Ask it "not spicy" if you want to get it actually quite spicy
Breakfast is amazing - various, fresh, tasty, in a large cozy canteen
The view from the 19th floor of the premium room. On the opposite side there are the twin towers but you can't see them behind the neighbor buildings

tip.text: The hotel's taxi is overpriced: to go to the nearest village (1km away) they'd ask 100bt - but you should pay 50bt. The same on the way back (divide the prices of locals minimum by 2).
The food in the hotel's resto is 3-4 times more expensive than if you go to the nearest village. Pay 50 bt each way (instead of 100bt which the hotel taxi demands), and it will still be cheaper
It's a very old, unmaintained dusty airport

tip.text: I was firstly flattered by the nice exterior and a pool, but then displeased by the room: it's not worth of its price, chick of 90's, old, especially bathroom. The linen & towels look old and dirty.

Very clean, modern and quite rooms, I enjoyed my stay there. A wide breakfast menu
